    "created_at": "2014-01-08T16:34:25Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-01-08T16:34:25Z",
    "body": "There's a real problem with using `#[unsafe_destructor]` in that no one understands why the destructor is unsafe. The compiler just says \"use this attribute\" and everyone goes ahead and uses it without understanding what's actually unsafe or what could be unsafe.\n\nI think we should either thoroughly document and improve the error message about unsafe destructors, try to not have unsafe destructors, or possibly some other route (a bound indicating the flavor of destructor?).\n\nHow would `UnsafeDrop` work? Would you be forced to drop the value in an `unsafe` block?\n",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
