    "created_at": "2014-01-08T16:38:01Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-01-08T16:38:01Z",
    "body": "It doesn't seem too unreasonable to me. The destructors _can_ be unsafe, if implemented incorrectly. The syntax could be a little different, but it seems very similar to an `unsafe { ... }` block (which almost all smart pointers need too).\n",
